fields.title: Gym
fields.content: I train 5 days a week, every week.

fields.title: Health
fields.content: The most important thing for every living thing is health. We experience life to its fullest when we are healthy in all aspects, i.e physical, mental, emotiomal and spiritual etc. Physical health is at its peak when we eat right, get enough sleep, excercise regularly and bath/keep clean regularly. Emotional health can be improved by taking care of the physical health, when you eat good, sleep well, excercise etc. you naturally feel good. But other methods involve being productive, spending time with loved ones and so on. Spiritual health is improved through meditation and yoga, there are other ways, but for me these are the best ways.

fields.title: Mathematics
fields.content: Mathematics is the language of the universe. Everything has to do with Math whether we are aware of it or not. A lot of people hated Math at school when I was growing up, even at college. Thankfully for me, it was the subject I loved the most out of all subjects I did. I loved it because I understood it. In elementary I would usually get awards in Numeracy, everyone knew that was MY award. When they would announce the winners of each award, 'Gabriel Katara' was a name that would be called for Numeracy, no one touched that award more than me in my classes back then. My love for Math fell in grade 9 where I completely lost interest in school, due to poor teaching by the teacher, but it was re-ignited when we got a new teacher who was very good at teaching. He knew I was smart in Math, so unsurprisingly, I was one of his favorite students. I still love Math now, years after graduating. I study it every now and then to keep up to par and not forget important concepts and fundamentals.

fields.title: Rap Music
fields.content: I am fan of rap music, it's my favorite genre of music. I grew up idolizing most of the rappers and artists in the music industry. I loved it due to the fact that their lifestyle and luxury intrigued me. I loved the fancy cars, the big masions they film at, and the stacks of cash. But all that is not real, these are not people to be idolizing because most of them do shady stuff to get that money and success. I respect people who make money in an honest way with more morale an consideration of other people's well-being. I still love rap music, it is still my favorite genre of music by far, but I do not idolize rappers or look up to them anymore. In fact, O do not care much about their personal lives.

fields.title: Rest API
fields.content: If you asked me what rest api was last year, I would look at you with a facial expression which would make it clear to you that I have no idea whatsoever, but things happen in life and people learn new things. 'People' is me, I learned how to code in python and then javascript, which made me come across APIs, particularly rest api, which I used when building this app. It's like the waiter in a restuarant that listens to your request and fetches the thing(s) you want. What an amazing servant it is, eh?

fields.title: Grand Theft Auto
fields.content: GTA is coming soon, in some months apparently. I am not really much of a gamer, but I have an interest in game development. It was once hacked and leaked online by some teenager in Europe/America, whatever happened to him I have no idea. But GTA is coming soon, gamers!

fields.title: Dirty Diana
fields.content: This was a great song by Michael Jackson. I knew the song for years, but it's only in the last couple of months that I managed to know its name. I knew it was a song by Michael Jackson, but never really knew the name of the song. I saw a video on a twitter thread and then knew instantly which song it is, then I also found the name of the song, finally.

fields.title: Electronics
fields.content: I am learning about electronics. I have done Electrical Technology in high school which helped, because I am familiar with most of terms used and also some of the components. I should know better, but at school we were learning to pass, not really to understand. There is a lot I learned at school that I have now forgotten. I learn better when I learn out of curiosity and on my own without having to study for some 'exam' paper or formal education credentials. I want to understand electricity at a deeper level.

fields.title: Time
fields.content: Time is the most valuable asset we have in this world. Time is more important than money (I know the broke dudes hate to hear this), because our lives consist of time, when you run out of time you die, but not with money. We go to school, spending 12+ years to gain skills and knowledge that will make us employable. We exchange time for a monthly salary. The employers know that the time of employees is more valuablr to them than what they lose paying them every month. Our time increases their freedom, and they will gladly pay for that. Time is precious, always spend your wisely.
